00:17:25,210 --> 00:17:29,480
He agreed without any hesitation.

253
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:33,020
He understands you're putting a lot of effort into this.

254
00:17:35,790 --> 00:17:37,780
The other day,

255
00:17:37,780 --> 00:17:40,470
he encouraged me for the first time.

256
00:17:42,380 --> 00:17:43,970
Did he?

257
00:17:45,510 --> 00:17:49,710
Have you ever been taught by your father?

258
00:17:49,710 --> 00:17:53,350
Well... occasionally.

259
00:17:55,050 --> 00:17:58,260
But his explanations are hard to understand.

260
00:18:01,490 --> 00:18:04,450
But those lessons only lasted

261
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:06,170
until my mother died.

262
00:18:10,270 --> 00:18:12,850
She got sick when I was in 8th grade...

263
00:18:14,570 --> 00:18:17,210
There wasn't anything we could do about it, but

264
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:21,860
he prioritized his work over nursing my mom.

265
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:26,860
He wasn't even there when she passed away.

266
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:29,880
<i>I called him so many times.</i>

267
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:32,990
<i>I was alone in her hospital room.</i>

268
00:18:32,990 --> 00:18:35,950
The flowers in her room

269
00:18:35,950 --> 00:18:38,480
seemed oddly beautiful.

270
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:44,250
<i>He must have thought of that moment every day.</i>

271
00:18:45,990 --> 00:18:48,610
He's an awful dad,

272
00:18:49,340 --> 00:18:52,010
but without his help,

273
00:18:52,970 --> 00:18:55,570
I wouldn't be able to go to cram school or even college.

274
00:18:56,310 --> 00:18:59,170
I want to become an adult fast.

275
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:08,820
After you pass the exam,

276
00:19:08,820 --> 00:19:11,940
let's confront your dad together.

277
00:19:11,940 --> 00:19:14,190
While you're a kid

278
00:19:14,190 --> 00:19:16,350
let's tell him everything flat out

279
00:19:16,350 --> 00:19:18,390
you couldn't till now.

280
00:19:19,990 --> 00:19:21,640
You can't do that,

281
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:23,940
since you're his son.

282
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:26,950
Harumi...

283
00:19:30,690 --> 00:19:33,340
Come on, let's go back.

284
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:40,950
What were you doing with Yamashita?

285
00:19:40,950 --> 00:19:43,550
- What?
- Where did you guys go on his motorcycle?

286
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:45,210
Did you see that?

287
00:19:45,210 --> 00:19:47,290
I thought you were showing off.

288
00:19:47,290 --> 00:19:49,530
He dropped you off right at the cram school.

289
00:19:49,530 --> 00:19:53,530
Well, that's...

290
00:19:53,530 --> 00:19:58,040
<i>Wait, why am I acting like his girlfriend who got caught on cheating?</i>

291
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:01,940
It was a date. We went on a date.

292
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:05,700
There isn't anything I can do for you on the exam day.

293
00:20:05,700 --> 00:20:09,650
I do go on dates, you know. I'm in my 30's.

294
00:20:12,390 --> 00:20:13,930
Bye.

295
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:29,600
Hey, Kyohei.

296
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:31,340
Are you drunk?

297
00:20:31,340 --> 00:20:33,680
What's wrong with that?

298
00:20:35,370 --> 00:20:39,350
You don't have to go to the University of Tokyo.

299
00:20:39,350 --> 00:20:43,190
It's pointless to go, totally.

300
00:20:43,190 --> 00:20:46,720
Just go easy on your study.

301
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:49,030
Average is the best way to go.

302
00:20:49,030 --> 00:20:51,650
The nail that sticks out gets hammered down.

303
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:57,490
Why would you say that?

304
00:21:01,410 --> 00:21:03,840
It's too late for that crap!

305
00:21:09,580 --> 00:21:12,360
- Yanagihara?
- Here.

306
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:13,990
Yuri?

307
00:21:17,140 --> 00:21:18,210
Did he tell you guys anything?

308
00:21:18,210 --> 00:21:21,700
He hasn't replied to my texts.

309
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:23,920
- He must be studying at home.
- Right.

310
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:26,920
He can probably focus better there than here!

311
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:29,110
Right?

312
00:21:32,510 --> 00:21:34,480
Here you go.

313
00:21:37,850 --> 00:21:40,370
It's easy to catch a cold or get distracted here.

314
00:21:40,370 --> 00:21:42,550
Not the best place to study.

315
00:21:42,550 --> 00:21:46,750
It's better to study at home or the cram school.

316
00:21:47,970 --> 00:21:53,060
Today I don't want to go home or to the cram school.

317
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:58,620
Did something happen with Jun?

318
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:03,990
Excuse me. It's a last call.

319
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:06,390
We'll be leaving.

320
00:22:15,260 --> 00:22:17,140
Want to come to my place?

321
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,540
Here.

322
00:22:24,330 --> 00:22:26,710
Sorry. Thanks for this.

323
00:22:26,710 --> 00:22:28,160
You're welcome.

324
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:33,400
I'll be working in the other room. Let me know if you need anything.

325
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:35,710
I will.

326
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:10,670
<i>[Good Job on the Law of Sine]</i>

327
00:23:10,670 --> 00:23:12,310
<i>[You did great! Everything before this is perfect!]</i>

328
00:23:12,310 --> 00:23:13,680
<i>[You have the basics down. Have confidence!]</i>

329
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:15,480
<i>[Careful! This could also be 270. Clarify the range of the unknown angle!]</i>

330
00:23:16,550 --> 00:23:21,970
<i>You've loved Harumi for so long.</i>

331
00:23:21,970 --> 00:23:25,090
<i>Has that ever turned into hate?</i>

332
00:23:29,090 --> 00:23:31,350
It must be nice for you.

333
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:35,220
You can love and hate Junko as you please.

334
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:39,170
Probably I'll...

335
00:23:39,780 --> 00:23:43,510
always be her dependable cousin for the rest of my life.

336
00:23:45,410 --> 00:23:50,200
As long as I'm her cousin, there's no love or hatred.

337
00:23:53,590 --> 00:23:56,640
She'll...

338
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:59,920
never see me as a man.

339
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:16,990
What? He missed school?

340
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:20,440
Yeah. I was wondering if he was studying at cram school.

341
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:23,620
No, he didn't have any classes with me today.

342
00:24:23,620 --> 00:24:26,600
He wasn't at the self-study room, either.

343
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:28,280
How did he do on the mock exam?

344
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:30,620
Probably it was Grade E.

345
00:24:30,620 --> 00:24:33,180
<i>So maybe he's feeling down.</i>

346
00:24:33,180 --> 00:24:35,120
<i>Or maybe he's taking a break?</i>

347
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:37,270
Yeah.

348
00:24:37,270 --> 00:24:40,240
I hope he's okay.

349
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:44,510
- You should take a break, too.
- What?

350
00:24:44,510 --> 00:24:46,650
How about a meal?

351
00:24:47,810 --> 00:24:49,040
Sure.

352
00:24:49,040 --> 00:24:52,010
Let me know what day works for you.

353
00:24:52,010 --> 00:24:54,470
- I'll see you then.
<i>- Okay.</i>

354
00:24:54,470 --> 00:24:57,140
Have a good night.

355
00:24:57,140 --> 00:24:59,250
<i>Good night.</i>

356
00:25:05,180 --> 00:25:08,600
Paw. Paw. Paw!

357
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:12,090
Masashi?

358
00:25:12,090 --> 00:25:14,130
Why... How'd you get in here?

359
00:25:14,130 --> 00:25:15,560
How?

360
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:20,350
I said "hi" to your parents and walked up the stairs.

361
00:25:20,350 --> 00:25:24,020
R-Right. That's how people normally come in.

362
00:25:24,020 --> 00:25:26,740
Not by climbing a fence.

363
00:25:26,740 --> 00:25:30,110
Were you talking to Yamashita?

364
00:25:31,130 --> 00:25:32,710
Yeah.

365
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:36,280
I see.

366
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,950
How did things go with Makise?

367
00:25:39,950 --> 00:25:44,650
I just took Yuri back home.

368
00:25:44,650 --> 00:25:46,340
What?

369
00:25:46,340 --> 00:25:48,750
He was studying in a cafÃ©.

370
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:52,820
I brought him to my place and he fell asleep while he was studying.

371
00:25:52,820 --> 00:25:54,880
Why was he at a cafÃ©?

372
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:58,330
He seems like he didn't want to talk about it, so I didn't ask.

373
00:25:59,130 --> 00:26:01,140
Did something happen?

374
00:26:01,140 --> 00:26:04,730
<i>What were you doing with Yamashita?</i>

375
00:26:10,310 --> 00:26:12,710
He's probably asleep, right?

376
00:26:14,390 --> 00:26:17,830
It's a crucial time for him to stay in a good headspace. Pay close attention.

377
00:26:17,830 --> 00:26:22,530
But I'm sure you know better than anyone.

378
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:25,450
Yeah.

379
00:26:26,980 --> 00:26:31,130
But I'm not sure how to act.

380
00:26:31,970 --> 00:26:36,200
I'm afraid he'll end up like me, if I pressure him too much.

381
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:40,460
I'm so confused.

382
00:26:49,590 --> 00:26:51,090
Okay.

383
00:26:53,610 --> 00:26:55,410
Harumi-sensei.

384
00:26:55,410 --> 00:26:58,040
Yuri won't be coming in today.

385
00:26:58,040 --> 00:27:00,410
What? Did he say that?

386
00:27:00,410 --> 00:27:03,580
I bet he was disappointed at the result of his mock exam.

387
00:27:03,580 --> 00:27:06,070
These things happen around this time.

388
00:27:06,070 --> 00:27:10,600
But would he skip school because of that?

389
00:27:12,940 --> 00:27:18,370
<i>[Sanno Seminar]</i>

390
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:23,940
<i>Currently unavailable...</i>

391
00:27:25,660 --> 00:27:28,800
What the heck is going on?

392
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:33,040
Dad. Hey, Dad!

393
00:27:51,250 --> 00:27:52,650
<i>[The University of Tokyo Study Guide]</i>

394
00:28:02,230 --> 00:28:04,410
<i>[Junko Harumi]</i>

395
00:28:12,650 --> 00:28:15,410
<i>Mr. Yuri?</i>

396
00:28:15,410 --> 00:28:17,970
<i>Is Shojiro Yuri there?</i>

397
00:28:17,970 --> 00:28:19,700
<i>General Director Yuri.</i>

398
00:28:19,700 --> 00:28:23,860
<i>Hello? General Director?</i>

399
00:28:23,860 --> 00:28:24,820
With that said,

400
00:28:24,820 --> 00:28:30,080
to put it simply, political events change the history of the world.

401
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:36,860
The world you live in today will also become a part of world history.

402
00:28:38,930 --> 00:28:40,920
Yamashita-sensei, a moment, please.

403
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:42,730
Okay.

404
00:28:42,730 --> 00:28:43,580
It's self-study time.

405
00:28:43,580 --> 00:28:45,790
<i>Hooray!</i>

406
00:28:45,790 --> 00:28:48,470
<i>There has been suspicion of bribery over a university establishment's approval.</i>

407
00:28:48,470 --> 00:28:50,890
- Bribery again?
<i>- Deputy Chief Secretary Yoshikawa</i>

408
00:28:50,890 --> 00:28:54,990
<i>has been suspected of giving illegal preferential treatment</i>

409
00:28:54,990 --> 00:28:57,860
<i>towards a university opening in 2020.</i>

410
00:28:57,860 --> 00:29:02,410
<i>It wasn't my doing. It was decided by the Ministry of Education.</i>

411
00:29:02,410 --> 00:29:07,830
<i>Deputy Chief Secretary Yoshikawa has been admitted to the hospital for a check-up this afternoon.</i>

412
00:29:07,830 --> 00:29:10,650
Unbelievable!

413
00:29:10,650 --> 00:29:14,930
In the case that the media inquires the school about Yuri...

414
00:29:14,930 --> 00:29:17,830
Wait, the news says he's been hospitalized.

415
00:29:19,030 --> 00:29:22,450
Politicians always use that as an excuse.

416
00:29:22,450 --> 00:29:24,020
Hospitalized?

417
00:29:24,020 --> 00:29:28,180
<i>General Director Shojiro Yuri of the Ministry of Education, who is in charge of approving university applications,</i>

418
00:29:28,180 --> 00:29:32,860
<i>is suspected of giving preferential treatment</i>

419
00:29:32,860 --> 00:29:36,900
<i>to Tohto University following Deputy Secretary Yoshikawa's instructions.</i>

420
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:40,090
Isn't that Yuri's father?

421
00:29:40,090 --> 00:29:42,710
- That's right.
- He is.

422
00:29:42,710 --> 00:29:45,190
Will he be all right?

423
00:29:45,190 --> 00:29:48,480
I think his father going to the University of Tokyo

424
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:52,040
may have been his motivation.

425
00:29:54,380 --> 00:29:58,070
Excuse me. I have to go now.

426
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:01,680
Mr. Yuri.

427
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:03,580
Generale Director Yuri.

428
00:30:04,460 --> 00:30:06,350
You're in there, aren't you?

429
00:30:06,350 --> 00:30:08,590
We know you're home.

430
00:30:08,590 --> 00:30:10,080
General Director?

431
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:13,870
You don't need to ring the bell over and over!

432
00:30:13,870 --> 00:30:15,620
Who might you be?

433
00:30:15,620 --> 00:30:18,480
What is your relationship with the General Director Yuri?

434
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:21,400
- What is the purpose of your visit?
- Excuse me. Please stop!

435
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:23,600
Can I ask you a few questions?

436
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:26,740
Keep your hands off her.

437
00:30:26,740 --> 00:30:31,590
You're causing a huge disturbance, so get out of the way.

438
00:30:40,850 --> 00:30:41,650
Yuri.

439
00:30:41,650 --> 00:30:44,020
- What's with that hair color?
- Pink hair?

440
00:30:44,020 --> 00:30:46,360
Please stop. He's unrelated to this case.

441
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:49,490
He's a minor. Please stop.

442
00:30:51,660 --> 00:30:54,220
Tell your father to come out now!

443
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:58,590
<i>I know he's in the house.</i>

444
00:31:03,020 --> 00:31:04,990
Please, excuse our intrusion.

445
00:31:06,750 --> 00:31:09,480
I'm sorry for causing you to worry.

446
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:13,620
I've been told to keep quiet and forced to take days off.

447
00:31:14,210 --> 00:31:18,420
Not that I can take a break with those reporters outside.

448
00:31:18,420 --> 00:31:22,490
It must be hard for you.

449
00:31:22,490 --> 00:31:26,750
I didn't want to get swept up in all this.

450
00:31:27,650 --> 00:31:32,180
But in the end, the bureaucrats will force me out of office.

451
00:31:32,180 --> 00:31:34,990
When I thought you were working,

452
00:31:35,570 --> 00:31:37,370
you were helping with their corruption.

453
00:31:37,370 --> 00:31:42,880
I didn't help them. I even don't know anything about the bribe.

454
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:47,340
Then why are you staying silent? You should tell the truth.

455
00:31:47,340 --> 00:31:50,780
You don't understand the world of politics.

456
00:31:53,860 --> 00:31:56,290
Then, will you just wait to get demoted?

457
00:31:58,620 --> 00:32:00,290
Will you be fired?

458
00:32:02,580 --> 00:32:04,350
Or arrested?

459
00:32:04,860 --> 00:32:06,750
Who knows?

460
00:32:08,060 --> 00:32:13,760
You abandoned Mom for work, and this is what you get for it?

461
00:32:14,720 --> 00:32:16,560
You're a fool.

462
00:32:30,850 --> 00:32:33,870
<i>Yuri, I'm coming in.</i>

463
00:32:48,900 --> 00:32:50,870
Yuri-yuri.

464
00:33:02,360 --> 00:33:03,980
I...

465
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:09,000
won't be taking the exam.

466
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:14,360
I quit.

467
00:33:16,070 --> 00:33:18,220
Why?

468
00:33:20,270 --> 00:33:22,670
I doubt that I will pass.

469
00:33:25,830 --> 00:33:30,140
Your father's problem and your exam are two different matters.

470
00:33:30,140 --> 00:33:32,760
You have to keep it together.

471
00:33:32,760 --> 00:33:35,630
Weren't you going to prove something to your dad?

472
00:33:37,350 --> 00:33:40,180
That's not all.

473
00:33:40,180 --> 00:33:43,050
We don't know for sure, if you have Grade E yet.

474
00:33:43,050 --> 00:33:48,120
As I said before, it's very common for high schoolers to score low.

475
00:33:48,120 --> 00:33:51,830
- You don't have to be so depressed.
- I said that's not all!

476
00:33:57,270 --> 00:34:00,050
Everything is all jumbled up in my head now.

477
00:34:02,080 --> 00:34:04,460
I can't think of anything.

478
00:34:06,470 --> 00:34:08,730
- Yuri-yuri.
- Yuri.

479
00:34:16,100 --> 00:34:18,510
You're teachers.

480
00:34:25,100 --> 00:34:27,270
Harumi-sensei.

481
00:34:31,160 --> 00:34:32,900
I'm sorry.

482
00:34:36,470 --> 00:34:38,740
I can't do this anymore.

483
00:34:43,430 --> 00:34:45,960
The reporters are outside.

484
00:34:47,820 --> 00:34:50,360
So please don't visit me again.

485
00:34:51,850 --> 00:34:53,850
You're a bother.

486
00:35:05,080 --> 00:35:07,070
<i>Junko?</i>

487
00:35:08,460 --> 00:35:10,320
<i>Mom.</i>

488
00:35:11,790 --> 00:35:13,740
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

489
00:35:15,090 --> 00:35:19,740
<i>I'm at my limit.</i>

490
00:35:46,590 --> 00:35:48,390
I'm sorry.

491
00:36:01,710 --> 00:36:04,850
Dad, Kazuma is here.

492
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:14,350
You have some nerve coming here.

493
00:36:14,350 --> 00:36:17,240
I'm sorry to visit you when you're having a rough time.

494
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:19,910
I should have visited you sooner.

495
00:36:19,910 --> 00:36:23,780
I told him not to come.

496
00:36:30,460 --> 00:36:36,270
Visiting at a time like this... What do you want?

497
00:36:36,270 --> 00:36:38,910
Dad, please be nice.

498
00:36:38,910 --> 00:36:42,750
He's not a man who visits to express his sympathy.

499
00:36:47,440 --> 00:36:49,860
I came to ask you

500
00:36:49,860 --> 00:36:54,870
to announce the truth about the university scandal.

501
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:58,550
What's it to you?

502
00:36:58,550 --> 00:37:03,730
Shojiro Yuri's son is my student.

503
00:37:04,510 --> 00:37:07,750
I see. Your student, huh?

504
00:37:11,750 --> 00:37:14,260
That has nothing to do with me.

505
00:37:14,260 --> 00:37:17,200
I know this is a lot to ask.

506
00:37:17,890 --> 00:37:19,910
Ask?

507
00:37:23,780 --> 00:37:29,990
Then I have something to ask of you. It's only fair, right?

508
00:37:35,500 --> 00:37:37,560
If you...

509
00:37:39,110 --> 00:37:41,640
are ready to do

510
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:47,650
the thing I want most.

511
00:37:49,310 --> 00:37:51,060
Which is?

512
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:56,670
Yuka, I want to lay down. Lower my bed.

513
00:37:57,780 --> 00:37:59,530
I'm home.

514
00:37:59,530 --> 00:38:01,550
